data.text:
The block-by-block clearing mechanism helps tokens find their fair market price and helps protect smaller bidders by reducing sniper advantage

Earlier participation also typically results in a better average price, aligning incentives between the token and users

The Continuous Clearing Auction Protocol helps avoid these outcomes by enabling market-driven price discovery:

+ Anyone can bid onchain
+ Bids clear continuously as blocks arrive
+ All winning bids within the clearing range get tokens

No offchain trust. Just aligned incentives. https://t.co/8EsBPA7lTl

Undersubscription and oversubscription are both symptoms of the same issue: price discovery happens outside of the distribution process

If it‚Äôs overpriced, users are less inclined to participate, which can lead to unhealthy market dynamics

If it‚Äôs underpriced, there's massive

When price is set offchain or in advance, two things tend to happen:

1) The market says the price is wrong
2) Users get stuck in a lottery for access

Token launches are having a moment

But most distributions miss the basics: fair price discovery, transparent allocation, and open participation

The Continuous Clearing Auction Protocol solves this, while being fully onchain
